The Australian police say the two men accused of carrying out a deadly shooting at a Jewish Hanukkah celebration at Sydney’s Bondi Beach that killed 15 people were “inspired” by the ISIL (ISIS) group. 
Public vigils honour the lives lost, with calls growing for stricter gun laws and stronger action against hate speech.

The nation is united in grief, focusing on remembrance and resilience in the wake of the tragedy.

Al Jazeera’s Danielle Robertson reports from the site of the attack in Sydney.

His victory marks a significant shift since the end of military rule more than three decades ago.

description:
Residents in Uvira have held a protest in support of M23 fighters, describing them as liberators and saying they feel safer under their control.
M23 says it is fighting for its community while also engaging in peace talks in Doha and the United States.
The group has announced plans to withdraw, but has not given a timeline or commented on the protest.
M23 insists any withdrawal must involve a neutral force, not a direct handover to the DR Congo government.
Some residents oppose pressure for a pullout and are calling for US forces to guarantee their security.
They warn they could block roads if the fighters leave without safeguards.
Fighting continues south of Uvira, raising doubts over when or how a withdrawal might begin.

Al Jazeera’s Alain Uaykani reports from the rally in Uvira, in DR Congo.

author: Al Jazeera English
description:
For more than a century, the nation-state has shaped how we organise the world, offering unity for some and division for others.

In this Doha Debates Town Hall, filmed live in partnership with the Bradford Literature Festival, we ask: Where does national belonging come from? Is it defined by culture and citizenship? Or does it go beyond the nation-state?

Moderated by Malika Bilal, this live debate brings together guests Shashi Tharoor, Wael Hallaq and David Engels, along with university students from Qatar Foundation’s Education City and beyond, to discuss the future of the nation-state on the same stage, in front of a live audience.

The views expressed in this episode are the guests’ own and do not necessarily reflect Al Jazeera’s editorial stance. Visit the @DohaDebates YouTube channel for the extended version.
